Class ExecutableWrapper<T extends Executable>

java.lang.Object
info.kgeorgiy.ja.koloskov.implementor.ExecutableWrapper<T>
Type Parameters:
T - the type of Executable (either Method or Constructor)
Direct Known Subclasses:
ClassImplementor.ConstructorWrapper, ClassImplementor.MethodWrapper
public abstract class ExecutableWrapper<T extends Executable> extends Object
An abstract wrapper for Executable elements such as methods and constructors.

This class provides functionality for generating code representations of executable elements, including their modifiers, return types (for methods), parameter lists, and exception declarations.

It serves as a base for specific wrappers like MethodWrapper and ConstructorWrapper

  • Field Details

    • DEFAULT_RETURN_VALUES

      protected static final List<ExecutableWrapper.DefaultValue> DEFAULT_RETURN_VALUES
      Default return values for primitive types.

      This list is used when generating method bodies with default return statements.

      The rules are applied in order, meaning that boolean returns false, void returns an empty statement, and any other primitive type returns 0.
